    "what_description": "Machaeranthera bigelovii is a perennial herbaceous plant native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico. It belongs to the family Asteraceae and is a member of the genus Machaeranthera. The plant grows up to 50 cm tall with a woody base and leaves that are linear, lanceolate, or oblanceolate, measuring 2-15 cm in length and 1-6 mm in width. The inflorescence is a corymbiform array of discoid heads, each containing 20-40 yellow or orange ray florets and 50-150 purple or pink disc florets. The plant produces achenes with a pappus of 20-40 barbellate bristles, 2.5-4 mm in length.",
