    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Machaeranthera bigelovii are its anti-inflammatory activity, which has been attributed to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones, a class of bioactive compounds that have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. This plant also exhibits antimicrobial properties, which can be attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, allowing it to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms. The anti-cancer activity of Machaeranthera bigelovii has been linked to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones and saponins, which have been shown to induce apoptosis in cancer cells and inhibit tumor growth. Additionally, this plant has been found to have antioxidant properties, which can be attributed to the presence of phenolic acids and flavonoids, allowing it to scavenge free radicals and reduce oxidative stress. The anti-diabetic activity of Machaeranthera bigelovii has been attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which have been shown to decrease glucose levels and improve insulin sensitivity.",
