    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Machaeranthera bigelovii are sesquiterpene lactones, primarily helenalin and 8-epi-helenalin, which have anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and cytotoxic properties. The sesquiterpene lactones in M. bigelovii have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes, such as cyclooxygenase-2 (COX-2), and to scavenge free radicals, thereby reducing inflammation and oxidative stress. The plant also contains flavonoids, including kaempferol and quercetin, which have antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities. Additionally, M. bigelovii contains phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, which have been shown to have antimicrobial and antioxidant properties. The combination of these constituents in M. bigelovii contributes to its potential as a natural remedy for various health conditions, including inflammation, infections, and oxidative stress-related diseases.",
